articles.description: BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) — Hungary's president has resigned amid outrage over her pardoning of a man convicted in a child sexual abuse case.
articles.title: Hungary's president has resigned amid outrage over her pardoning of a man convicted in a child sexual abuse case

articles.author: NAJIB JOBAIN and SAMY MAGDY
articles.description: RAFAH, Gaza Strip (AP) — Israeli airstrikes killed at least 44 Palestinians — including more than a dozen children — in the southern Gaza city of Rafah on Saturday, hours after Israel's prime minister said he had asked the military to plan for the evacuation of hundreds of thousands of people there ahead of a ground invasion.
articles.title: Israeli strikes kill 44 Palestinians in Rafah after Netanyahu says ground invasion is coming there

articles.author: STEVE PEOPLES, ZEKE MILLER and SEUNG MIN KIM
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — President Joe Biden's Democratic allies are launching an aggressive defense against a special counsel's explosive claims that the 81-year-old president couldn't remember major milestones in his life, trying to diminish the significance of the prosecutor's allegations that Biden was too forgetful to be charged for mishandling classified material.
articles.title: How Biden and his allies are pushing back against a special counsel's claims about his memory

articles.author: MICHAEL GOLDBERG
articles.description: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) — Diversity initiatives would be defunded or banned from universities and other public institutions under a slate of bills pending in Republican-led legislatures, with some lawmakers counting on the issue resonating with voters in this election year.
articles.title: Republican lawmakers are backing dozens of bills targeting diversity efforts on campus and elsewhere

articles.author: BASSEM MROUE and ABDULRAHMAN ZEYAD
articles.description: BEIRUT (AP) — An Israeli drone strike hit a car near Lebanon’s southern port city of Sidon on Saturday, killing at least two people and wounding two others, security officials said.The strike came as tensions across the Middle East grow with the Israel-Hamas war, a drone attack last month that killed three U.S.
articles.title: An Israeli drone strike in Lebanon kills 2 in one of the deepest hits inside the country in weeks

articles.description: BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) — Hungary’s conservative president has resigned amid public outcry over a pardon she granted to a man convicted as an accomplice in a child sexual abuse case, a decision that unleashed an unprecedented political scandal for the long-serving nationalist government.
articles.title: Hungary's president resigns over a pardon to a man convicted in a child sexual abuse case

articles.description: NAPLES, Fla. (AP) — Moments before a private jet slammed into a Florida highway, the pilot calmly told an airport controller that the aircraft “was not going to make the runway” since it had lost both engines.
articles.title: 'We've lost both engines,' pilot says before private jet crashed onto Florida interstate, killing 2

articles.author: LAURAN NEERGAARD
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Any parent who’s ever called one of their children by the other’s name — or even the family pet’s name — likely could empathize when President Joe Biden mixed up the names of French leaders Macron and Mitterrand.
articles.title: Verbal gaffe or sign of trouble? Mixing up names like Biden and Trump have done is pretty common

articles.author: FOSTER KLUG
articles.description: TOKYO (AP) — Will she make it in time?Taylor Swift's last song was still ringing in the ears of thousands of fans at the Tokyo Dome on Saturday night when the singer rushed to a private jet at Haneda airport, presumably embarking on an intensely scrutinized journey to see her boyfriend, NFL star Travis Kelce, play in the Super Bowl in Las Vegas.
articles.title: Taylor Swift expected to make epic journey from Tokyo to the Super Bowl. Will she make it in time?

articles.author: LEANNE ITALIE
articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — Elise Plessis hasn't been in a long-term relationship for 26 years. It's by choice, yet she still suffers FOMO when Valentine's Day rolls around.“I'm the singleton of the family and the friend group,” said the 53-year-old Plessis, who lives in Manitoba, Canada.
articles.title: Here's how to beat the hype and overcome loneliness on Valentine's Day
